    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into large, bite-size pieces</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of salted boiling water and cook for 10 min or until almost fork-tender</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to another pot of <strong>salted</strong> water, bring to the boil and cook for 8 min</p><p>Once done, cool the egg[s] by running them under cold water</p><p>Tip: cooling the eggs completely makes them easier to peel!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>olives</strong> roughly</p><p>Cut <strong>tomato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges, then cut them in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> - this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>green beans</strong> to the <strong>potatoes</strong>, cover and remove from the heat</p><p>Leave the pot off the heat for 4 min or until the potatoes are cooked and the beans are bright green and al dente (retaining a bite)</p><p>Drain and return the potatoes and beans back to the pot, off the heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> to the <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>beans</strong> and give everything a gentle mix</p><p>Peel and quarter the cooled <strong>egg[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>lettuce</strong> into bite-size pieces</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-nicoise/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Assemble your salads with a layer of lettuce, the potatoes, green beans, then scatter the olives over, followed by tomatoes and egg</p><p>Break the <strong>mackerel</strong> over the top (peel off the skin and discard), then drizzle with the <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
